# Creating Journal Pages

When creating a new journal page, follow these steps in order:

## 1. Reference the Template

Always start by reading `journal/template.html` to understand the current page structure, styling, and component usage. Use this as the foundation for any new journal page.

Key elements from the template:
- Inter font preloading and loading script
- `<site-nav>` component for navigation
- Menu open/close event handlers for dimming content
- Consistent typography and spacing classes
- Article structure: `.article-header`, `.article-content`, `.article-footer`

## 2. Create the Journal Page

Create a new folder under `/journal/` with a URL-friendly name (lowercase, hyphens instead of spaces):

```
/journal/[page-name]/index.html
```

Include:
- Appropriate `<title>` tag: "Article Title | Rob Boyett"
- Correct `datetime` attribute on the `<time>` element
- RSS feed link in the head
- All necessary images/assets in the same folder

## 3. Update journal.xml (Navigation Menu)

After the page is complete, add an entry to `/journal.xml` for the site navigation dropdown.

Add a new `<entry>` element near the **top** of the file (newest entries first):

```xml
<entry>
    <title>Article Title</title>
    <url>/journal/page-name/</url>
    <preview>/journal/page-name/</preview>
</entry>
```

Note: The `<preview>` element typically matches the `<url>` for local journal pages.

## 4. Update feed.xml (RSS Feed)

Add a new `<item>` element to `/feed.xml` after the `<lastBuildDate>` tag (newest entries first).

```xml
<item>
    <title>Article Title</title>
    <link>https://robboyett.com/journal/page-name/</link>
    <guid>https://robboyett.com/journal/page-name/</guid>
    <pubDate>Day, DD Mon YYYY 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
    <description>A brief description of the article for RSS readers.</description>
</item>
```

Also update the `<lastBuildDate>` to the current date.

### Date Format Reference

RSS dates use RFC 822 format:
- `Mon, 06 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000`
- Day names: Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri, Sat, Sun
- Month names: Jan, Feb, Mar, Apr, May, Jun, Jul, Aug, Sep, Oct, Nov, Dec

## Checklist

Before considering a journal page complete:

- [ ] Page created at `/journal/[page-name]/index.html`
- [ ] Title and date are correct
- [ ] `<site-nav>` component included
- [ ] Menu event handlers set up
- [ ] Entry added to `journal.xml`
- [ ] Item added to `feed.xml`
- [ ] `<lastBuildDate>` updated in `feed.xml`
- [ ] All images/assets are in the page folder
